2. Soracte, Virg. Aen. 11. 785, hod. ‘Monte S. Oreste'; a mountain of Etruria, 2,420 feet high, about twenty-six miles north of Rome. Its striking outline, separated from the main range of the Sabine hills by the broad Tiber valley, makes it a conspicuous feature in all northern views across the Campagna.
